		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>This paper discusses the factors contributing to the choice of beam stay-clear (BSC) in DIAMOND. The lifetime which results from this definition is then calculated to ensure that it is adequate for the operation of the machine. The BSC is defined using a semi-empirical approach by calculating the requirement for a momentum acceptance of at least 4% at all locations around the lattice. Allowance for injection and closed orbit errors also contribute to the overall BSC.</p>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
